children.subject: Any idea when we'll hear back about specifics (schedules) of our duties?

Just a note, I expect that students who have taken 189 in the past will actually learn a *lot* by being involved in course staff. We're adjusting the material to hopefully bring out some concepts more clearly and more deeply, as well as really leveraging what the lower-division provides. This will have the side-effect of allowing the course to significantly grow its treatment of more contemporary material, including more on neural nets.  It should be a great learning experience for students.

history.content:
Calling all former CS 189 students:

 

On behalf of the Fall 2017 CS 189 staff, I invite you to apply for our Academic Intern role. Academic Interns organize and run guerrilla sections, and help out during homework parties/office hours. We welcome anyone who has taken CS189 to apply.

 

You will have the option to receive units, if you choose to serve for a minimum number of hours per week. Also, note that we prioritize notable academic interns when making TA recommendations to the professors.

 

Please find the application here

(The deadline is August 31st.)
